itunesNotes.standard: Sketches Pro? It’s just like the Tayasui Sketches app we’re so enamored with… except it comes with layers, extra tools, and all sorts of expert features. If you’re a serious artist—or a longtime doodler like us—you can’t do better than Tayasui.
itunesNotes.short: Create artwork using outstanding sketching tools.
From quick conceptual sketches to fully finished artwork.

itunesNotes.standard: Inspiration tends to strike when you least expect it—heck, some of our best ideas come to us in the shower—and Procreate is a dazzling way to snatch sparks of visual genius out of the ether and bring them to life. Behind the app’s slick drawing and painting tools are robust features that you’d expect from a full-fledged illustration package—it even has the ingenious ability to use your Apple Watch as a color palette picker. If a brilliant notion does strike in the shower, though, get out and dry off.

advisories: Infrequent/Mild Alcohol, Tobacco, or Drug Use or References

itunesNotes.standard: Coloring. It’s fun, creative, and just for little kids. Right? Wrong. Once you get your hands on this virtual coloring book—designed for adults—you’ll wise up to this one simple fact: we never should have quit. Each illustration is wonderful designed, and we loved switching between watercolors, colored pencils, and pens to make every piece unique.
itunesNotes.tagline: Let colors say what's in your heart
